      "writtenOn": "2020-08-22T00:23:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Your suggestion is simple and elegant. I only have one concern -- do we need to support -F like ssh in future? If so, I cannot rely on the base dir in ResolveHostFromFiles because the path can be from anywhere. I have tested with ssh that it will only look at ~/.ssh in this case. Here is an example:\n\nseewaifu@seewaifu:~$ cat t.conf\nInclude abc.conf\n\nseewaifu@seewaifu:~$ cat .ssh/abc.conf\nHost abc\n    HostName 127.0.0.1\n    Port 2223\n    User root\n\nseewaifu@seewaifu:~$ cat abc.conf\nHost abc\n    HostName NonExistingHost\n    Port 2223\n    User NonExistingUser\n\nseewaifu@seewaifu:~$ ssh -F t.conf abc\nPassword: \nlocalhost ~ # exit\nlogout\nConnection to 127.0.0.1 closed.\n\nssh will pick up abc.conf from .ssh instead of my home directory. \n\nThe change is simple, but I do want to discuss a little bit first. Thanks.",
      "parentUuid": "b9f60a59_3b9156fa",
