      "writtenOn": "2020-08-21T05:33:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This name is a bit surprising to readers because it\u0027s not obvious how to resolve a path to multiple paths. Readers can know that the former \"path\" can contain wildcards after reading comments, but it\u0027s much better if the function signature explain it.\n\nProperly naming things and consistently call them in established names is a key to make code readable. In this case, I really recommend naming \"paths with wildcards\" differently than mere \"paths\", and using the term consistently throughout the code.\n\nFor example, you can decide to use \"glob\" for path-with-wildcard (you can pick any term that makes sense). If we do so, we can rename like:\n\n func resolvePathToPaths(f, baseDir string)\n -\u003e\n func resolveGlobToPaths(glob, baseDir string)\n\n func readFiles(configFileName, baseDir string, ...)\n -\u003e\n func readFilesByGlob(glob, baseDir string, ...)\n\nand so on.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 247,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 247,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "25a7b89ba13db41735f87cded32b14c61c89cc97",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e2819b89_e6f83e5d",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/internal/sshconfig/sshconfig.go",
