      "writtenOn": "2020-08-21T05:33:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why don\u0027t you just make them two separate unit tests? In general it\u0027s good to keep a unit test concentrate on verifying a single thing so that test failures are easy to interpret and they can run in parallel.",
